<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="CH1a0930" type="notes"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Research Notes for 鬼谷子</title><editor role="creator">TLS Project</editor></titleStmt><publicationStmt><p>published electronically as part of the TLS project at https://hxwd.org</p><availability status="2">This work has been licensed for use in the TLS</availability></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><bibl><title>Research Notes</title></bibl><p>Comments and notes to <bibl corresp="#CH1a0930"><title xml:lang="och">鬼谷子</title></bibl>.</p></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><creation resp="#CH">Initially created: <date>2022-03-01T01:26:01.485+09:00</date> by CH</creation></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div><head>Comments</head><p xml:id="CH1a0930-start"><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-08-02T15:32:07.408+09:00">粵若 yuèruò also appears in HS, HHS and SuiS; the expression refers to the literary past.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:50:31.602+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:50:22.836+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:50:10.72+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2024-07-24T21:37:39.502+09:00">Not "Pforte des Seins und des Vergehens", but possibly "machttechnischer Zugang zu dynastischer Kontinuität und dynastischem Niedergang" (avenues to dynastic continuity and decline). Check parallels to 存亡 and 門戶 in legalist texts, e.g. HFZ.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:49:50.083+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:49:44.504+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:49:33.813+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:49:26.321+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:49:19.265+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:49:09.656+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:49:02.254+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:48:55.086+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:48:45.131+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:48:36.155+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2023-01-10T17:29:19.462+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2023-01-10T17:29:23.062+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-01-01T18:48:11.339+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2024-07-24T22:09:44.643+09:00">as for duó quán, "assess one's authority/influence", compare 聖人審權以操柄 in SJS: legalist influence?</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2024-07-24T22:26:05.888+09:00">In fact, this is a topicalization (new topic in non-narrative sentence) of 賢、不肖、智、愚、勇、怯: As for the worthy and unworthy, ..., they differ in terms of moral principles such as benevolence and righteousness. Xu Fuhong, who emended the text and deleted 仁義, must not be followed here.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2024-07-24T22:36:43.669+09:00">無為以牧之: reinterpretation of the legalist catchword 牧, "to shepherd (the people)" (cf. Guanzi, Chao Cuo, etc.) from a laissez-faire, non-interventionalist perspective.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2024-07-24T22:45:15.673+09:00">compare legalist concepts of power, e.g. in SJS</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T17:08:17.062+09:00">cf. note to 知存亡之門戶 earlier in this chapter.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-5a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:11:37.333+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-5a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:11:47.427+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-5a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:11:50.88+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-5a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:11:54.013+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-5a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:18:33.64+09:00"/><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-5a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:08:41.058+09:00">cf. earlier notes to 門戶</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-3a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-08-01T16:49:43.217+09:00">Tsao: In the Yijing, the hexagrams 乾 and 坤 are the first two to appear and stand for "open"/"close" and "heaven"/"earth", respectively.</seg></p></div></body></text></TEI>